@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{b} WB use @{ub} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BFermer" "Close gadget"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}Close gadget @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
When you click in this gadget, Convaski sleeps until you reactivate it by
double-clicking on its AppIcon on the Workbench screen.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BZoom" "Zoom gadget"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}Zoom gadget@{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
When you click on the gagdet zoom, the window is reduced to its title bar.
You have to click again on this gadget to resize the window to its original
state.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BAide" "Help..."
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}@{u}H@{uu}elp... @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
A first click brings the help requester. Another one ends the help mode.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BApropos" "About..."
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}@{u}A@{uu}bout... @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Some information about the @{"author" LINK "Adresse"}.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BOuvrir" "Open..."
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}@{u}O@{uu}pen... @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Click to get a file requester in order to choose a file or a drawer.@{PAR}
You can convert a whole directory. For this, no file name must be written in the
File gadget in the file requester. You can get a drawer requester by holding
down the shift key while you're clicking on Open...@{PAR}
Please note that the pattern gagdet content [generally #? or ~(#?.info)] will be
used as a filter. For example, just imagine you wrote:@{LINE}@{JCENTER}
c#?s@{LINE}@{JLEFT}
in the Pattern gagdet. In this case, Convaski will only convert filename
beginning with c and ending in s (case is irrelevant).@{PAR}
For further information on how to use pattern, please see your AmigaDOS manual.@{PAR}
You can also drag a file or a drawer icon on the Convaski window (where you
want, except on the `Viewer' or `To' gadgets zones).@{PAR}
@{PAR}
See also: @{"FROM=" LINK "IFROM"}.

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BAfficheur" "Viewer"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}Vie@{u}w@{uu}er @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Enter the name of your preferred text viewer here. Please write the complete
path to it. Default: sys:utilities/more (unless you modify the @{"VIEWER" LINK "IVIEWER"} tool
type).@{PAR}
@{PAR}
See also: @{"VIEWER=" LINK "IVIEWER"}.

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BVoir" "View"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}@{u}@{u}V@{uu}iew @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Launches the @{"viewer" LINK "BAfficheur"} to see the currently selected file content.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BComm" "Convert"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}@{u}C@{uu}onvert @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
To begin the conversion of the file or of an entire drawer. Don't forget to
check the @{"direction" LINK "BSens"} of the conversion and the @{"memory" LINK "BMÕmoire"} settings.@{PAR}
If a drawer is to be converted, a request will pop up to ask for a confirmation.
You can jump this by holding down the shift key while clicking on Convert.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
See also: @{"NOCONFIRM" LINK "INOCONFIRM"}.

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BSens" "Direction"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}@{u}Di@{u}r@{uu}ection @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
To choose the direction. Quite simple. In `Psion -> Amiga', Psion actually
refers to the IBM (?) 850-2 codepage. This character set is used in, of course,
the Psion but also in the Canon StarWriter models (at least tested with the 30
one).@{PAR}
@{PAR}
See also: @{"DIRECTION=" LINK "IDIRECTION"}.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BGuill" "Curved quotes"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}Curv@{u}e@{uu}d quotes @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
If you want the converted file with smart quotes on the Mac or on the PC, tick
this gadget.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Example. The sentence:@{LINE}
@{CODE}
The guy says: "Who wrote: 'Nuclear tests are f... dangerous'?"

will be converted in

The guy says: ``Who wrote: `Nuclear tests are f... dangerous'?''
              ^^           ^                                  ^^
              ||           |                                  ||
|₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤|₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤
+-->  This will be only one character on Mac or PC.
                           |
    Please note the direction of the single quote.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BAuto" "Auto"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}A@{u}u@{uu}to @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
This function allows the program to automatically detect any changes made on the
choosen file for the conversion. When such changes are detected, the conversion
begins alone in the background.@{PAR}
(Option not available when a drawer was chosen.)@{PAR}
NOTEZ BIEN. Some file sytems (CrossDos one, for example) do no support this
feature (called `notification'). In such a case, a requester will appear.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
See also: @{"WINDOW=" LINK "IWINDOW"}, @{"AUTO" LINK "IAUTO"}, @{"FROM=" LINK "IFROM"}.

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BMÕmoire" "Memory"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}@{u}M@{uu}emory @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{b}Normal.  --@{ub} The file to convert is completely loaded in memory before
conversion. Some problems can arise with very large files: see next option.@{PAR}
@{b}Minimal. --@{ub} All is done as the conversion goes. The file is read byte
after byte. Best option when files are in the RAM disk.@{PAR}
@{b}Maximal. --@{ub} Everything occurs in memory. A temporary file is created
(see @{"TEMPDRAWER" LINK "ITEMPDRAWER"}).@{PAR}
@{PAR}
See also: @{"MEM=" LINK "IMEM"}.

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BDeVers" "From & To"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}From @{ub}&@{b} @{u}T@{uu}o @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
`From' shows the file or the drawer you chose with Open or you dragged onto the
window. The name of the future converted file appears in `To' preceded by `Cvg_'
(or what you @{"choose" LINK "IPREFIX"}).@{PAR}
@{PAR}
See also: @{"FROM=" LINK "IFROM"}, @{"TODRAWER=" LINK "ITODRAWER"}.

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BProgr" "Progression"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}Progression @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Shows the progression in percent.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BArrõter" "Stop"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}@{u}S@{uu}top @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
To... stop the conversion.@{PAR}
If a drawer was being converted, you'll be asked to choose between a total stop
or a partial stop.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BFichier" "File being converted"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}File being converted @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Place where the name of the file being converted is written.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BQuitter" "Quit"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}@{u}Q@{uu}uit @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Guess!@{PAR}
Note that a click on the @{"close gagdet" LINK "BFermer"} DOES NOT quit the program. Only the QUIT
button can be used for that.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BI" "i"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}@{u}i@{uu} @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
This gadget puts up a requester with some information on the file or drawer in
the @{"From" LINK "BDeVers"} gagdet (name, protection flags [sparwed], size, comment]).@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BT" "d"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}@{u}d@{uu} @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
To change the destination drawer. Option not available when a drawer was
specified in @{"TODRAWER" LINK "ITODRAWER"}.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

