@NODE "Optic¶ne" "Tool types settings"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{b} Tool types settings @{ub} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
To set these tool types, click on the Convaski icon and choose `Information...'
in the Icons menu.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{"APPICON=" LINK "IAPPICON"}@{PAR}
@{"APPICONX= et APPICONY=" LINK "IAPPICONXY"}@{PAR}
@{"AUTO" LINK "IAUTO"}@{PAR}
@{"BIP" LINK "IBIP"}@{PAR}
@{"DIRECTION" LINK "IDIRECTION"}@{PAR}
@{"FROM=" LINK "IFROM"}@{PAR}
@{"MEM=" LINK "IMEM"}@{PAR}
@{"NOCONFIRM=" LINK "INOCONFIRM"}@{PAR}
@{"PREFIX=" LINK "IPREFIX"}@{PAR}
@{"PUBSCREEN=" LINK "IPUBSCREEN"}@{PAR}
@{"QUOTES=" LINK "IQUOTES"}@{PAR}
@{"REQUESTDRAWER=" LINK "IREQUESTDRAWER"}@{PAR}
@{"TEMPDRAWER=" LINK "ITEMPDRAWER"}@{PAR}
@{"TODRAWER=" LINK "ITODRAWER"}@{PAR}
@{"VIEWER=" LINK "IVIEWER"}@{PAR}
@{"WINDOW=" LINK "IWINDOW"}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
If the option is within parentheses [e.g. (QUOTES=YES|NO)], Convaski will no see
it. If you want the option to be activated, get rid of the parentheses and write
only one option: QUOTES=NO.

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{b} Tool types settings @{ub} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IMEM" "MEM="
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}MEM= @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
NORM or MINI or MAXI. See @{"Memory" LINK "BMÕmoire"} for a detailed explanation.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IVIEWER" "VIEWER="
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}VIEWER= @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Write the name of your preferred viewer (path included).
Default: sys:utilities/more.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "INOCONFIRM" "NOCONFIRM"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}NOCONFIRM @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
This option disables various warning requesters in Convaski (no warning before
writing to a yet existing file, etc.).@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IDIRECTION" "DIRECTION="
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}DIRECTION= @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Write after the = the number (1 to 7) corresponding to the direction of the
conversion you want:@{PAR}
1.   Amiga      -> Macintosh@{PAR}
2.   Amiga      -> PC-Windows@{PAR}
3.   Macinstosh -> Amiga@{PAR}
4.   Macintosh  -> PC-Windows@{PAR}
5.   PC-Windows -> Amiga@{PAR}
6.   PC-Windows -> Macintosh@{PAR}
7.   Psion      -> Amiga@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IQUOTES" "QUOTES="
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}QUOTES= @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
YES (if you want a @{"`clever'" LINK "BGuill"} conversion of the quotes) or NO.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IREQUESTDRAWER" "REQUESTDRAWER="
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}REQUESTDRAWER= @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Write the path where you want the file requester to first open. Default: ram:.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IWINDOW" "WINDOW="
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}WINDOW= @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Three possibilities:@{PAR}
1. WINDOW=SLEEP. Convaski starts up but opens no window. An AppIcon is
nevertheless still present on the WB screen. Interesting when used with @{"AUTO" LINK "IAUTO"} 
and @{"FROM" LINK "IFROM"} since Convaski will only open a small window during the
conversion.@{PAR}
2. WINDOW=ZIP. Convaski opens its main window but in its `zipped' state (only
the title bar remains).@{PAR}
3. WINDOW=YES. Option by default.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "ITEMPDRAWER" "TEMPDRAWER="
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}TEMPDRAWER= @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Write the path of the place in which you want the temporary file to be created
when the option @{"`Memory: Maximal'" LINK "BMÕmoire"} is used. Try to choose
a fast medium with enough free room.@{PAR}
Default: T: (i.e., if you changed nothing, a drawer in the RAM disk).@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "ITODRAWER" "TODRAWER="
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}TODRAWER= @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Write the drawer in which EVERY file converted will be put.@{PAR}
Default: the same drawer as the file to be converted.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IBIP" "BIP"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}BIP @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
If you want a beep at the end of the conversion.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IPREFIX" "PREFIX="
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}PREFIX= @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
You can change the three letters before the file name of the converted file.
Default: Cvg. An underscore (_) will be added after your own letters.@{PAR}
Examples :@{PAR}
@{b}If the file name is...           If PREFIX=          If PREFIX=testing @{ub}@{PAR}
TextME                           _TextME             tes_TextME@{PAR}
somethingelse                    _somethingelse      tes_somethingelse@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IPUBSCREEN" "PUBSCREEN="
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}PUBSCREEN= @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
The Convaski window always opens on the Workbench screen. If you prefer it
to open on a public screen, write the public screen name with this tool type.
Be careful: from WB 2.0 to WB 3.0, case is significant when choosing a public
screen name (no more with 3.1).@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IFROM" "FROM="
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}FROM= @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
To choose the initial content of the `From' gagdet.@{PAR}
See @{"AUTO" LINK "IAUTO"} to understand this function utility.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IAUTO" "AUTO"
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}AUTO @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Why this tool type? Let's see it. First you choose a file with @{"FROM" LINK "IFROM"}. Then you
ask Convaski to use the @{"Auto" LINK "BAuto"} option by using this tool type. Your file is
then ready to be converted without any further manipulation. You can even use
@{"WINDOW=SLEEP" LINK "IWINDOW"} to prevent Convaski from opening its main window!@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IAPPICON" "APPICON="
@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}
@{PI}
@{b}APPICON= @{ub}@{PAR}
@{PAR}
The Convaski AppIcon is Convaski's own icon. But if you prefer another one, put
its name here, WITHOUT the .info extension.@{PAR}

@{PARI 0}@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}@{JCENTER}@{BG FILL}[ @{" Contents " LINK "main"} @{" WB use " LINK "Atelier"} @{" Tool types settings " LINK "Optic¶ne"} @{" Address " LINK "Adresse"} ]@{BG BACK}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE

